@database HexEditClass
@index "Classes.guide/Main"

@Node Main "RxMUI - HexEdit Class"


HexEdit class    @{"Index" link "Classes.guide/Main"} @{"Super" link "VirtgroupClass.guide/Main"}
@{u}                                                             @{uu}

  HexEdit class is used to create a gadget to edit memory.

  HexEdit class is a subclass of HexEdit.mcc, so you must have
  HexEdit.mcc in MUI:Libs/MUI to use it. HexEdit.mcc is copyright
  of Miloslaw Smyk.

  A HexEdit object is very dangerous if you don't really know
  what you are doing!

  @{u}                                                        @{uu}

 @{b}Attributes@{ub}

  @{fg shine}ActiveField@{fg text}
  M G2N ISGN
  A number or one of:
     o HexDump
     o Chars

  @{fg shine}AddressChars@{fg text}
  M ISGN G2N
  A number or Auto

  @{fg shine}BaseAddressOffset@{fg text}
  N IS
  A boolean that indicates if the first address should
  be offset to 0.

  @{fg shine}BytesPerColumn@{fg text}
  N IG

  @{fg shine}BytesPerLine@{fg text}
  N SGN

  @{fg shine}ByteValue@{fg text}
  B SGN

  @{fg shine}ColumnsPerLine@{fg text}
  M IG G2N
  A number or Auto

  @{fg shine}CursorAddress@{fg text}
  N SGN

  @{fg shine}CursorNibble@{fg text}
  N ISGN

  @{fg shine}CursorVisible@{fg text}
  B ISGN

  @{fg shine}EditMode@{fg text}
  B ISGN

  @{fg shine}First@{fg text}
  N ISGN

  @{fg shine}FirstLine@{fg text}
  M S
  One of:
     o Up or -1
     o Down or -2
     o PageUp or -3
     o PageDown or -4
     o Top or -5
     o Bottom or -6

  @{fg shine}FullRefresh@{fg text}
  B S

  @{fg shine}HighBound@{fg text}
  N IG IND
  A 4 bytes max long packet chars string (e.g. '7eeeeee'x) upper
  address of the mem to edit. Note that a wrong address may cause
  enforcer hits.

  @{fg shine}LowBound@{fg text}
  N IG
  A 4 bytes max long packet chars string (e.g. '7eeee00'x) lower
  address of the mem to edit. Note that a wrong address may cause
  enforcer hits.

  @{fg shine}MoveCursor@{fg text}
  M S
  One of:
     o Up or -1
     o Down or -2
     o Left or -3
     o Right or -4
     o PageUp or -5
     o PageDown or -6
     o Top or -7
     o Bottom or -8
     o WordLeft or -9
     o WordRight or -10
     o LineStart or -11
     o LineEnd or -12

  @{fg shine}NibbleValue@{fg text}
  N SGN

  @{fg shine}PropObject@{fg text}
  S IS
  A Scrollbar object name. Note that at Init time the object have
  to exists.

  @{fg shine}SelectMode@{fg text}
  M IG G2N
  A number or one of:
     o Nibble
     o Byte

  @{fg shine}VisibleLines@{fg text}
  N GN

  @{u}                                                        @{uu}

 @{b}Methods@{ub}

  None defined

  @{u}                                                        @{uu}

 @{b}Examples@{ub}

    1. A HexEdit object without Scrollbar:
      mem=GetSpace(1024)
      if mem=Null() then exit
      call Export(mem,Copies("RxMUI rulezzzz!!!",50))
      ...
      he0.Class="HexEdit"
      he0.Frame="Virtual"
      he0.EditMode=1
      he0.LowBound=mem
      he0.HighBound=d2c(c2d(mem)+1023)

    2. A HexEdit object with Scrollbar:
      mem=GetSpace(1024)
      if mem=Null() then exit
      call Export(mem,Copies("RxMUI rulezzzz!!!",50))
      ...
      sg1.Class="group"
      sg1.Horiz=1
      sg1.Spacing=0
       sg1.0="he1"
        he1.Class="hexedit"
        he1.Frame="Virtual"
        he1.EditMode=1
        he1.LowBound=mem
        he1.HighBound=d2c(c2d(mem)+1023)
        he1.PropObject="Scroll1"
       sg1.1=XNewObj("Scrollbar","Scroll1")

    3. A HexEdit object with Scrollbar in the right window border:
       if mem=Null() then exit
       ...
       win.UseRightBorderScroller=1
       ...
       mem=GetSpace(1024)
       if mem=Null() then exit
       call Export(mem,Copies("RxMUI rulezzzz!!!",50))
       ...
       sg2.Class="group"
       sg2.Horiz=1
       sg2.Spacing=0
        sg2.0="he2"
         he2.Class="hexedit"
         he2.Frame="Virtual"
         he2.EditMode=1
         he2.LowBound=mem
         he2.HighBound=d2c(c2d(mem)+1023)
         he2.PropObject="Scroll2"
          Scroll2.UseWinBorder="right"
        sg2.1=XNewObj("scrollbar","Scroll2")

@EndNode
